a bad dye job for the wolf in sheep's clothing. i don't know what made me draw this last night. it made sense today as i read a friend's account of sexual assault, and re-experienced all my trauma. the thing about normalised abuse is that one knows in one's heart that it wasn't okay but might not know how to process it then. in some cases, even the assaulter knows that it's not okay. but much thanks to a systemic normalisation of such trauma, it subtly creeps up on you unwarned, it slowly and steadily steals quality of life from you until you either completely shut it down or look it in the eye and confront it and take your power back. unless you don't do it, you don't realise what all you were missing out on and what all you were suffering with. as i shared with my friend today, the beauty of the #metoo movement is that while individually most of us were suffering, going through  dehumanisation every now and then; we never knew the horrors each one of us has witnessed up until now, we could never heal together. her story empowered me today to confront someone from my past, who i would be reminded of each time i read a woman's story, and take my power back. for all the tears that i have shed in at least the past two weeks, i realise that it is never too late to stand up for oneself. i also learnt yet again in a differing context that avoidance and blocking of memory doesn't ever heal as much as standing up for oneself does. if you've gone through something, speak up, don't silence yourself. you need not follow others way of healing themselves, find a way that works best for you. share and talk to someone you trust or directly confront that person. whatever makes you feel better and whatever feels right. i am here to listen too.
â€¢â€¢â€¢

text:
"so, this happened back in december, 2017. the 28th day of the month.

it was around 10:30 in the night, when my sister and i were on our way back home, from the gym, when i suggested we take home momos for dinner, because we had both been talking about how much we crave them, two nights before this happened.

now, even though i live in what is supposed to be one of the "safer" parts of dwarka, new delhi there is a street exactly behind my building, where the street lights almost never are working. our regular momo vendor used to put his stall up, over there. 
thinking of the street lights not working as something very normal (because we've been using this particular street for going around for almost fifteen years now, and i have hardly any memories of it being well lit), my sister stopped the car (which was barely six months old, back then) in front of the stall, left the headlights on, and we ordered our usual, while still sitting in the car.

there was a grand i10 parked right in front of our car, on the wrong side of the road (such that the man in the driver's seat sat facing me and the man in the passenger seat sat facing my sister, who was driving), in which were seated two middle-aged men. the headlights of this car were shut. this also did not seem alarming.

a few minutes later, the man seated in the passenger seat of this car got out of the car, walked up to the window of the driver's seat, and using gestures, asked my sister to roll the window down. she refused to do so, as she wasn't very comfortable with the idea of it. after having the man plead repeatedly, my sister rolled the window down a tad and asked the man what he wanted. "aap apni gaadi ki headlights off kar dijiye," he asked my sister, to which my sister replied, "nahi, i am not comfortable". after three rounds of him asking to do so, and my sister refusing to do as the man asked, the man stopped and went back to his car and said something to the man in the driver's seat, immediately after which, this man switched on the headlights of his car, hoping that the same would hurt our eyes and make us switch the headlights of ours." (contd. in the comments)

text:
crying into a pillow case
heart broken from a severe case
of â€œwhy canâ€™t things just go my wayâ€
near drowning from the tears
confronted by the kinds of fears
that chase hopes and dreams away 
on the surface it appears
that these are tears of sadness
but that perception isnâ€™t reality 
these are tears of passion
she knows failure is a minor setback
so it fuels her motivation 
to get back to dream chasing 
so she picks herself up
dries her tears and never looks back
she refuses to breathe any doubt air
and needs no pats on the back
she is brave, strong and determined to
make her reality & dreams the same thing
.
.
.

text:
i started my journey of discovering my dream in 2005. it was 3 hard years of discovery (and faith, no money, confusion, getting made fun of) -- and then one day i started gaining some momentum.
.
then i finally realized what my dream/purpose is in 2008, but of course--it couldn't be that easy -> it got shot down at that company in 2009 bc of a #metoo thing.
.
so now, it's 2018. that is 10 years of knowing my dream and not being able to get it running...
.
that's hard y'all.
.
it's hard sleeping at night when you know you could be helping...
.
it's hard getting shot down after you finally feel like you've found the right person at a company to make it happen (which takes about a year and a half!) and then get the response that, "this is a great idea, we just don't have time to make it happen."
.
but it's also been a blessing...
.
when life hasn't been working in my favor, i had something to focus on other than whatever was going on.
.
i'm hoping this year, 10 years since i started chasing it, that it will finally, finally happen.
.
i call my idea social ingenuity, which is kind of a play on the toms shoe model, but doing it on a global level with major players.
.
for just one group, it could literally help more than 58 million people.
.
link in bio. thanks for the support and love - 9 chapters, 45 mins.

text:
thrilled to be a part of this #literary conference. details @mosaicmagazine. my panel:
1-2pm
#metoo & the movement
black women writers conjuring in the continuum 
in 2017, the #metoo campaign amplified the voices of survivors of rape, sexual assault and harassment. though social media platforms became the route to shared survivor stories, creating heightened awareness, accountability, and solidarity in response to a pervasive rape culture that is generations-deep, black women writers have courageously confronted patriarchal violence on the page while simultaneously experiencing a spectrum of abuses and violations in our personal lives. this panel, inspired by the break beat poetsâ€™ black girl magic anthology, as well as other creative collaborations and alliances, will continue this urgently important conversation. through this community dialogue,we will explore the continuum of black women writing against all that would attempt to violate our lives. we will elevate our stories, our activism, our labor, and lineage. 
panelists: jp howard, keisha-gaye anderson, and diamond sharp. facilitator: nina angela mercer
#writersofinstagram #writerscommunity #writerslife #womenwriters #africanamerican #blackwriters #poet #author @stillnina_love  @jphoward_poet

text: shared decision-making and informed consent are at the heart of the care we provide at fika midwifery. we believe that women are experts in their bodies, and their values toward pregnancy, birth, and parenting are to be understood and respected. the process of shared decision-making and consent usually involves the following process: first, either the midwife or the client introduces a topic (for instance, gbs screening and prophylaxis). we give the woman and her support people a brief overview of the evidence and recommendations from major certifying organizations and provide resources for further reading and research. at the next visit, we discuss any questions the expectant person may have and consider the research in light of personal values, medical history, and any other unique circumstances. we support the woman in receiving all of the information she needs to make a decision, and then we support her decision. we reassure her that if new information or a concern arises that may mean reconsidering the original plan, we will keep her informed. a critical aspect of shared decision-making and informed consent is time! although this example reviews prenatal decision-making, it can easily be applied to well-woman care, labor, postpartum, breastfeeding, and newborns. #shareddecisionmaking #informedconsent #fikamidwifery

text:
she was raped. 
call her a rape victim not a "survivor". they say that survivor is empowering, strong. it rolls off the tongue in a way that â€œvictimâ€ does not.Â "survivor" doesn't accurately sum up her experience. 
though the physical pain and rainbow of bruises did eventually fade, the impact of her rape never really did. "survivor" sugarcoats the reality of rape. "survivor" tells an ultimately hopeful, inspiring, empowering story. look at them, thriving despite violence.

they do not want to be the focus. they want the crime to be the focus. they want the criminal to be the focus. when we hear the term victim, we think about the crime, acknowledge its perpetrator. when we hear the term survivor, the perpetrator is erased.

text:
guess who's back..
after dealing with a big breakdown in late march this year, finally feeling a little better. took a break from all socialmedia, spend 3 months in a mental hospital and 1 month in a day clinic, but finally home and slowly starting to get everything in order. still gotta figure a few big and little things out over time, but as @jaredpadalecki said 'always keep fighting'. i'm stronger than ever and i will manage. sadly my mental illness goes hand in hand with selfharm, exhausting mood swings, big insecurities about myself and my actions, depressed thoughts, thinking about committing suicide and great fear of loss. also featuring post traumatic stress disorder, childhood abuse, verbal and physical, sexual abuse and many other traumas still to battle. but i will fight through and overcome everything. because i'm strong, independent, young, wild, free. finally also changing my name from celine guerreiro dudenhausen to kim-celine costa guerreiro. my life is finally about to start for real and nothing will stop me now.
#dreppressions #manicdepressiv #mentalillnessesarenotajoke #mentalillnessesrecovery #mentalillnessesarereal #mentalillnesseswarrior #alwayskeepfighting #akf #iamenough #imnotalone #fightingmydemons #iwillgetbetter #metoo #abuse #verbalabuse #physicalabuse #sexualabuse

text:
part 2 of article â€œdurgaâ€ : â–ªï¸
-
it was only when this one individual opened up to me, did i realise the hell that she had to cross through and overcome to be sane enough to talk to me over a cup of coffee. i was shocked, ashamed and above all i felt powerless, my heart racing and eyes being teary as she tried her best to recount all the instances where she had almost given up on life. i wanted to hug her and say that everything is fine, that no one would ever dare do anything to her anymore, that i would always be there for her no matter what. but in reality, she was perfectly still and sturdy like a mountain, it was me who was shaking uncontrollably and shattered into pieces. thatâ€™s when i realised that the one sitting across the table sipping the coffee while being perfectly calm, the one who had overcome the scars left by the monsters, the one who was now a guiding light to hundred of others, she was the real durga. i was just the guy who had come face to face with reality and realised how cruel the world can be. the issue of woman safety is real, every fourth girl around you must have faced one or the other instance where she almost believed that she may not live to see another day. if we as a collective do not take any action against this monster that has been feeding on us and ruining us, then eventually humanity would have reached a point where we will fail to realise the real enemy among us.â–ªï¸
-

text:
for around three weeks now, a number of indian women, particularly media and entertainment industry professionals, have come out with their experiences of being sexually harassed and raped over the years by male colleagues with the #metoomovement..
maitrimanthan also took a step forward and got a chance to represent women rights and harassment at workplace at inox udaipur. ms.monika sharma communicated about the issues women are facing at their workplace and how to prevent such issues. it was a complete bunch of discussion with employers and employees.
we are glad that all enterprises and other organizations are taking harassment issues on a serious note, and seeing prevention before action. ğŸ™

text:
you hold my heart fragile in your hands
these minutes count like hours now
and every day brings this closer
it took a while to clear my head
went out for hours and wept for everything that i couldn't know yet
as i lay this life in these hands now
don't you break these hearts of mine
and i brace myself
i will brace myself for everything that i don't know yet
it's really been no time at all
but every hour feels like days now
this is a life i'd bargain for
these moments slip through our fingers like grains of sand
never to be lived again
mere reflections of their eternal worth
echoes that sound on long after we are gone
am i to believe that there is more to this
as i stand before you here with open arms
facing up to nothing less than higher hopes @minor_victories

text:
then hate me when thou wilt; if ever, now;
now, while the world is bent my deeds to cross,
join with the spite of fortune, make me bow,
and do not drop in for an after-loss:
ah! do not, when my heart hath â€˜scaped this sorrow,
come in the rearward of a conquered woe;
give not a windy night a rainy morrow,
to linger out a purposed overthrow.
if thou wilt leave me, do not leave me last,
when other petty griefs have done their spite,
but in the onset come: so shall i taste
at first the very worst of fortuneâ€™s might;
and other strains of woe, which now seem woe,
compared with loss of thee, will not seem so.

text:
men have been telling women to shut up for at least 3,000 years.
~800 b.c.
in homerâ€™s the odyssey, as beard points out, odysseusâ€™ son telemachus tells his mother, penelope, to â€œgo back up into your quarters. speech will be the business of men.â€
~100 a.d.
if menâ€™s voices all suddenly turned female, greek orator dio chrysostom asks his audience, â€œwould not that seem terrible and harder to bear than any plague?â€
8 a.d.
in ovidâ€™s metamorphoses, philomela, the princess of athens, is raped by her sisterâ€™s husband, tereus. he advises her to stay silent, and when she lashes out, he cuts out her tongue.
1553
â€œwhat becometh a woman best, and first of al: silence. what seconde: silence,â€ thomas wilson writes in the arte of rhetorique.
1970s
before becoming pm, britainâ€™s margaret thatcher takes voice lessons. â€œsoon the hectoring tones of the housewife gave way to softer notes and a smoothness that seldom cracked,â€ writes charles moore.
1989
disneyâ€™s the little mermaid, in which ariel gives up her voice to win over a man, heralds a trend: in the next five disney princess films, male characters have three times as many lines as females do.
2011
apple introduces siri. microsoft follows with cortana, and amazon with alexa. â€œfemale voices are seen, on average, as less intelligent than male voices,â€ notes clifford nass, an authority on computer-human interactions. but for traditionally gendered tasks such as secretarial duties, â€œfemale voices are easier to hear.â€
2013
ceos with deeper voices manage bigger firms, and make significantly more money, than their higher-voiced peers, a much larger study concludes.
2018
christine blasey ford testifies at a senate judiciary committee hearing about her alleged sexual assault by supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh when they were teenagers. ford tells the senators that kavanaugh put his hand over her mouth to stifle her cries for help as he groped her: â€œthis is what terrified me the most, and has had the most lasting impact on my life.â€ a few days later, trump ridicules ford and declares that men are under siege in the face of the #metoo movement. â€œthink of your son!â€ he exclaims. â€œthink of your husband!â€
.full article on motherjones.com

text:
this year we supported @fpacharity's sexual health week which was on consent. the conversation about consent doesn't stop there though, and it doesn't stop when your partner consents to one kind of sex or sexual act with you.  consent should be a continuous conversation between you and your partner - it doesn't have to be difficult. here are a few phrases you could try to make sure you and your partner are on the same page throughout your sexual experiences:

is this ok?
does that feel good?
should we carry on like this?
would you like to try something else?
can i touch you here?
would you like to try this?

what should you do if your partner isn't checking in with you and is trying something you're not into during sex. you could have been quite happy earlier and are worried about spoiling the mood. first things first, if you're not comfortable, the mood is already spoiled. ways to broach it with your partner might vary according to what's happening - you could try something like "this is uncomfortable for me. i was really turned on by what we were doing earlier, i'd like more of that". you could also say something like "i'd like to stop doing this". then you can follow up with a chat after to discuss how you'd like to approach trying new things in future - having conversations about sex when you're not actually having it can be a really helpful way of talking about your mutual likes and establishing what you're comfortable with.
.
.
.
#consent #sexualwellbeing #healthyrelationships #communicationiskey #letstalkaboutsex #metoo #timesup #boundaries #oktosay #nomeansno #youdoyou

text:
a recent conversation brought back some repressed memories that then proceeded to drag me into a realm of darkness that i promised i'd stay out of.
.
if you're reading this,my dear culprits, do not be alarmed. there will be no name calling here or painfully excruciating details ( however i assure you, i remember every. little. thing). this is not about you. or what you did. this is about the aftermath. this is about the consequences of your actions.
.
i remember being branded a liar. i remember being told to keep quiet to maintain my honor. i remember being forced into denial- by myself and others. i remember blaming myself. i remember being unable to properly converse with any man. i remember being vary of even shaking a man's hand. i remember the feeling of wanting to clean my vagina with a bar soap, body wash, shampoo or literally anything else, no matter how bad it stung just so i could feel pure again. i remember stopping my prayers in tears because i felt like they wouldn't count anymore. i remember feeling like a disposable piece of trash that could just be used and discarded. i remember feeling utterly weak and helpless. i remember being distrustful of anyone and everyone. i remember trying to overcompensate to seem normal. i remember feeling like i was being judged every time i saw some victim blaming. i remember begging god to give me enough strength to forgive you. i remember feeling like a bad person after i couldn't forgive you. i remember scribbling down my suicide note with an inkpen i had just started to use. i remember wanting to wear the baggiest clothes i could find.
.
.
i. remember. everything.
.
i. will. always. remember.
.
i still get nightmares with you in them. i still have flashbacks that make me want to vomit. i still gag a little when i see your picture sometimes. i still have issues with physical intimacy amongst friends. i still have times when i wish you could go through my pain.
.
.
i will probably always be tainted by what you did. i know this. i have known this for a long time.
.
.
but i forgive you. not for you, but for myself. i forgive and sincerely pray and hope for you to be better.
.
.

text:
my sexual/verbal abuse:
from 6th grade till 9th grade i was sexually assaulted. not just physically but verbally as well.
from anonymous people to people i trusted. 
the mental scar it made on me is unthinkable. i hated my body. i hated people. and most importantly i hated boys and men. i was a little girl, unaware of what had been actually done to me those 4 years. 
no women should ever feel worthless and hate her body because of a person doing damage to her. i will carry this shame for the rest of my life but knowing how strong i am, one day i can overcome it. i used to be told to "cover the fuck up" why? apparently a women shouldn't show her curves and beauty to the world. i did the opposite. my strong character showed even more skin. it made me feel powerful when men were trying to shame me. it's no one's business how a person dresses. and no way in hell is a valid excuse "she was asking for it." go to hell with that! there is no excuse to sexually assault or abuse anyone. no one is worthy of any pain afflicted on them.
#metoo

text:
koffee with karan is back!

the favorite show of all times koffee with karan is ready to make a comeback on our television screens this sunday, 21st october. the wave of excitement and anticipation was unleashed after karan johar announced the bollywood reigning queensâ€™ deepika padukone and alia bhatt as his new seasonâ€™s first guests. 
as expected, johar has made sure that he teases his audience with everything that is going to happen on this season with latest confessions, juicy gossips, and upcoming weddings. over the years, the show has seen some of the major controversies and continued to wow the audience with new games, eloquent set, and the biggest highlight: huge coffee hamper. moreover, there are always discussions on social issues, the highs, and lows of bollywood, but this time around we hope to hear about #metoo movement and casting couch that has taken the film and media industry by storm.
this time coffee will be getting strong and spicy with hottest new parings as some of the episodes have already been shot with father-daughter duo saif ali khan-sara ali khan, star siblings arjun kapoor-janhvi kapoor, powerhouse performers ranveer singh-akshay kumar and the talented aamir khan.

text:
image source :google  as i  come out 
doesn't matter what type of clothes i wear : short or long 
million x-ray-eyes scanning me out .
if we let open lids of our hearts 
our woes will fill this beautiful sky  which hangs all day and night 
as if everything is alright. 
fear in days and suffused sloth and sullen expectations whole night.
" there is really no such thing as voiceless 
there are only the deliberately silenced or 
preferably unheard.(arundhati roy) "

text:
she hides in the dark.
she slinks in the shadows.
she clutches the cross to her bosom,
and chants his name over and over.
she watches as a hundred eyes watch her.
burning through her clothes,
grunting and moaning in helpless lust.
she quickens her pace,
but the shadows follow close behind.
they close the drapes,
they smear the sun,
leave her bleeding the poison of their sin.
damaged and ravaged she lies,
by the stink of the drain,
and drops her cross into it.
she finally understands.
the is no god.
there is no devil.
there are but us, cursed, damned,
to be alone...
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
if this year has taught us anything, it is that sexual assault is going to be called out, and more then likely other women are going to support you...except maybe if you have a disability.
individuals with an idd are seven times more likely to be raped or sexually assaulted than those of us without one. i've sat with women who have an idd that have had a rape kit done and yet they still won't talk because they feel that they have no support. because we, as a society have not been including them. they feel underrepresented in the movement.
for women without disabilities, the rapist is a stranger 24 percent of the time, but for a woman with an intellectual disability, it is less than 14 percent of the time. (npr source) meaning it is by someone they know, a lot of the time a caregiver, employer, or family member. we all know what trauma does to us physically, it is even worse when you have been taught compliance and do not have the language to express it. while i get that this is a dark subject, it is essential because elections are coming up, and i see so many people using their voices for change. talking about equal rights for women, poc, lgbtq, but yet i haven't seen a lot of mention of the disability community. so when you decide to post about the #metoo movement or use your voice to create change, remember the 6.5 million people in the population that tends to get left out. also, if you are going to tell me that you are proud of me for speaking up, i am just going to turn around and tell you that you should be speaking up more. #disabilityrightsarehumanrights

i may not finish inktober, but i felt like this was important to make.
because screw feeling like i have to feel scared of walking alone any time of the day.
screw feeling like i have to walk with my head down when i get yelled at.
and screw the fact that this is supposed to be normal.
im not a piece of meat, and nor are other women. 
and screw people who think women are lying when they actually do get assaulted. this stuff is happening all the time, and if you cant see the problem, then you are part of the problem.
.
.
.

i was out when this book arrived in my mail box and i was surprised by the aesthetics of the same. the title called out to me. in an era when #metoo is becoming the next rule of revolution, feminism has struck out with vigor and more fervor... how to distinguish the right from the wrong? how the surf reach mystery, talk about it and reveal the flaws? how to find the bad apple in a perfectly filtered grove? 
where are all the pretty vile girls hiding? ğŸ£ğŸ‘ ğŸ’„âœ¨ğŸ© this book insists on a swift, leave you panting, panties and power, control and discoveries, battering narrative of the most needed kind. no mincing, no munching. sexual predatory, abortion issues, social shock, bicuriosity, the female psychology, anti heroine phenomenon, objectification, the art of the story in backward format... there is a presentation of supposed facts but then the author quickly erases and writes over them. â™£ï¸
â™£ï¸
â™£ï¸
â™£ï¸ @reekycoleslaw weaves a bold story. unflinching. the characters can get to you. that's a pretty positive as well as negative point here. the book can be termed as another bollywood masala. some people might find it generic when it comes to writing of an indian society in all it's indian-ness and expositions. 
i have read quite a bit of my share of some really good thrillers and murder mysteries so i can say this isn't the best of my reads this year but yes, it packs a punch. @bloomsburyindia has done an amazing job with the presentation and it's a book which i had gift to thrill seeking junta. it has everything in terms of entertainment. the dialogues don't drag and the circumstances don't seem too much out of hand. 
read it if you like a multi thriller. a pretty girl, a vile vile world. 
i rate this book âœ¨âœ¨âœ¨/5

text:
(1/3) this account started as an accompanying piece to an exhibition for one of my design courses. in my personal life, iâ€™d been using my personal instagram account as a refuge of sorts. only accounts that brought inspiration or happiness were allowed a place on my newsfeed, but i realized that it had the potential for so much more. -

at the time, harvey weinstein was just beginning to be exposed, and #metoo started trending. i was frustrated with the lack of understanding and empathy that seemed to be shaping the conversation around these topics. and so, lets__talk__about was created. when used thoughtfully and purposefully, social media has the power to incite change.

text:
as part of our second annual film festival, we are proud to announce the following: 
the celebrating women panel and networking event! we will have an exclusive screening of the â€œi am christine blasey ford projectâ€ directed by skyler barrett and a special screening of the short film â€œceciliaâ€ directed by sophia moghaddam kiapos

during the panel we will discuss important topics including what is next after the me too movement. how to keep our sets/workplace safe and holding each other accountable. equal pay, gender and ethnic equality. supporting female filmmakers more! 
there will be assorted appetizers, refreshments and an excellent opportunity to for networking and celebrating our accomplishments and goals! 
our panelist include: 
sophia kiapos
skyler barrett
ann patricia
julie ann johnson
candice vernon
deena adar
elizabeth blake-thomas 
yvonne m. bernard

it will take place thursday - november 1, 2018 at the marriott courtyard old towne pasadena 180 n fair oaks, pasadena, ca 91103

tickets $10 (pre-sale) $15 at the door 
this is for a non-profit organization all proceeds go towards the non-profit. 
https://www.eventbrite.com/e/female-filmmakers-fuse-celebrating-women-tickets-50423527127

"time's up" 
time's up on waiting
time's up on silence
time's up on tolerating, discrimination, harrasment or absue..
the three deadliest words in many parts of the world are "it's a girl"
but i believe we can change that.
i stand for the generation where the full rights of girls and womens will be fulfilled everywhere because women's rights are human rights and vice versa.
because of this 200million girls are missing.
that 200 million fewer changemakers, doctors, mothers, teachers, wives.
they've been abandoned, murdered, raped, neglected, unwanted.
we stand for justice.
we stand for change. 
also,
it's not just a women problem.
it's community problem
women are not only the victims,
men too have been raped, assualted, murdered.
ending sexual and gender based equality voilence is everyone's responsibility.

text:
in one picture, eamon is watching some men work on our neighbor's roof. in the other picture, he is watching the business on our curious street. between the local restaurant, the school a few houses down, and our neighbor's daily activities, our street gets some decent action. as my son was alone in his bedroom watching the workers, i couldn't help but wonder, are they working hard? are they doing a right, honest job? are they treating each other well? are they saying things a 1-year old should learn to say?
the workers may, or may not know he is watching them and listening to what they say through the poorly insulated window. would their actions change if they knew he was there? i hope not. i hope that they are acting the way they would in front of a 1-year old, whether they knew he was seeing them or not. pure, blameless, strong, and honest. 
out the second window, he sees many police, ambulance, and fire truck vehicles rush by. he sees kids walk to and from school. he sees customers dining at the restaurant, eating and drinking.
he sees the old and young, rich and poor, happy and sad, all come hoping to fill their bellies at the restaurant. but as some people are saving lives, there are some risking their lives, and my son's life. they risk it by smiling as they gently and delicately light a cigarette. they risk it by paying for a drink that will alter their mind, their mind that should stay clear so they can conduct themselves in a right and controlled manner, so they never lack understanding and wisdom. they risk it by walking around with defeated bodies and faces. 
they risk my son's life because he is learning what to do, how to live, and who to become. why is he learning how to light a cigarette from watching it happen many times across the street? why is he learning that the way to relax and escape his life stressors and problems, or even just to have a good time, he must decrease his mind's ability and possibly put his body and others in danger? why is he learning that the person to become is defeated, sad, and hopeless?
be blameless and productive, even after you are dead. for a little boy might be watching you from his bedroom window.

text:
hot news
tertuduh lakukan pelecehan seksual, lara dutta batalkan proyek kerjasama dengan mukesh chhabra ğŸ˜¯

lara dutta menolak untuk bekerja dengan mukesh chhabra setelah dia dituduh melakukan pelecehan seksual.

sebelumnya hari ini mukesh chhabra telah di keluarkan dari tugas penyutradaraannya dalam proyek film "kizie aur manny" setelah banyak tuduhan pelecehan seksual, dan sekarang lara dutta juga menolak bekerja untuk perusahaannya.

setelah beberapa kali tuduhan pelecehan seksual yang dilontarkan terhadap mukesh chhabra, agen casting bollywood, fox star studios, produser dari film kizie aur manny, remake resmi hollywood hit the fault in our stars, menangguhkannya dari film. tidak hanya itu kemarin, laporan pelanggaran seksual pada set kizie aur manny oleh teman dekatnya dan bintang film sushant singh rajput sedang melakukan putaran media sosial. laporan itu juga menyatakan bahwa mukesh mengetahui pelecehan itu tetapi tidak melakukan apa pun.

sekarang, beberapa jam yang lalu legenda tenis mahesh bhupathi mengambil ke media sosial dan berbagi pemikirannya tentang gerakan #metoo yang sedang berlangsung. dalam catatan panjang, antara lain, ia mengungkapkan bahwa istrinya, mantan miss universe dan aktris lara dutta didekati oleh perusahaan mukesh chhabra untuk pekerjaan akting untuk platform digital. namun menurut mahesh, setelah diskusi internal, dia menolak untuk memberdayakan perusahaan mukesh dan mengatakan kepada platform digital yang sama. 
dalam catatan itu, ia juga menyebutkan bagaimana teman dekat lara, sajid khan, juga berada di bawah kasus pelecehan tersebut. sajid khan telah mengarahkan lara di filmnya, housefull. dan kemudian menyatakan bahwa dia mengakhiri semua hubungan dengan terdakwa tentabg semua ini seperti suhel seth, sajid khan, vikas bahl, anirban blah, chetan bhagat dan anu malik. dan juga didesak dari orang lain untuk #stopengaging dengan pria yang dituduh.

#timenownews 
#laradutta @larabhupathi
#mukeshchhabra

stop_filter_tweet: hot news teuduh lakukan pelecehan seksual , lara dutta batalkan proyek kerjasama dengan mukesh chhabra ğŸ˜¯ lara dutta menolak untuk bekerja dengan mukesh chhabra setelah dia dituduh melakukan pelecehan seksual . sebelumnya hari ini mukesh chhabra telah di keluarkan dari tugas penyutradaraannya dalam proyek film `` kizie aur manny '' setelah banyak tuduhan pelecehan seksual , dan sekarang lara dutta juga menolak bekerja untuk perusahaannya . setelah beberapa kali tuduhan pelecehan seksual yang dilontarkan terhadap mukesh chhabra , agen casting bollywood , fox star studios , produser dari film kizie aur manny , remake resmi hollywood hit fault stars , megguhkannya dari film . tidak hanya itu kemarin , laporan pelanggaran seksual pada set kizie aur manny oleh teman dekatnya dan bintang film sushant singh rajput sedang melakukan putaran media sosial . laporan itu juga menyatakan bahwa mukesh mengetahui pelecehan itu tetapi tidak melakukan apa pun . sekarang , beberapa jam yang lalu legenda tenis mahesh bhupathi mengambil ke media sosial dan berbagi pemikirannya tentang gerakan yang sedang berlangsung . dalam catatan panjang , antara lain , ia mengungkapkan bahwa istrinya , mantan miss universe dan aktris lara dutta didekati oleh perusahaan mukesh chhabra untuk pekerjaan akting untuk platform digital . namun menurut mahesh , setelah diskusi internal , dia menolak untuk memberdayakan perusahaan mukesh dan mengatakan kepada platform digital yang sama . dalam catatan itu , ia juga menyebutkan bagaimana teman dekat lara , sajid khan , juga berada di bawah kasus pelecehan tersebut . sajid khan telah mengarahkan lara di filmnya , housefull . dan kemudian menyatakan bahwa dia mengakhiri semua hubungan dengan terdakwa tentabg semua ini sepei suhel seth , sajid khan , vikas bahl , anirban blah , chetan bhagat dan anu malik . dan juga didesak dari orang lain untuk dengan pria yang dituduh . arabhupathi

text: â€œi graduated from drama school recently. as the culmination of two years of hard work, we put on a full-scale theatrical production. i played a sex worker, a young woman who was a victim of human trafficking. at one point during rehearsals, our director became angry with me for not sexing the part up enough. in the scene, this woman was asking a doctor for help, but a language barrier made some amount of physical storytelling necessary. the director became frustrated and in front of my scene partner and the stage managerÂ said i should just grab my breastsÂ and gestured the way in which he thought i should shove my breasts up into my face. he accused me of being afraid to go there, treated me like a bad actor, and acted as though i was just being difficult because i insisted that was wrong for the character and unnecessary.â€ â€” c, 25 #nodickpics #timesup #metoo #endsexualharassment #nomeansno #instaactivist #nofilter #instaxphoto #feminist #wontstayquiet #wontbeavictim #iamasurvivor #iamasurvivornotavictim #breakthesilence #endsexualassault #endsexualabuse #sexualassault #sexualharassment #staywoke #activist

text:
alaska native women and children are at much higher risk of domestic violence than the rest of the country. i have traveled all over the state, and have heard story after story from first alaskans. i heard several more of those stories this week at the afn convention.
___
we know that many indigenous communities have few resources to help overcome drug and alcohol addiction. we know that many have little to no law enforcement. we know that many have suffered intergenerational trauma for decades and are still struggling. i thank every person who has lifted their voice and their pain in order to get the attention of our leaders, despite how much those voices have historically been silenced and ignored.
___
domestic violence is personal to me. hereâ€™s my story. and hereâ€™s my promise to elevate your voices in washington to get things done for first alaskans in crisis.

we know that many indigenous communities have few resources to help overcome drug and alcohol addiction. we know that many have little to no law enforcement. we know that many have suffered intergenerational trauma for decades and are still struggling. i thank every person who has lifted their voice and their pain in order to get the attention of our leaders, despite how much those voices have historically been silenced and ignored.
___
domestic violence is personal to me. hereâ€™s my story. and hereâ€™s my promise to elevate your voices in washington to get things done for first alaskans in crisis.

text:
honoured and humbled to play music with my partner @maxzt  for asia initiatives' event last night where 
ex-un secretary- general ban ki-moon presenting the women's empowerment award to chelsea clinton and susan blaustein for their extensive work for women's rights. thanks to geeta & krishen mehta for this opportunity and for making me a part of your endeavour. 
like so many of you, i've been deeply triggered by the overwhelming amount of women coming out with their stories of harassment. i'm a survivor of sexual abuse and as i navigate this difficult time learning every day just how much deception and misogyny this world holds; it meant everything to be surrounded by these powerful and strong forces fighting for women's empowerment and standing up for what is right. it was exactly what i needed, to pick myself up and continue to fight for justice and for an equal and safer world for women. 
please look up these organisations and support them! 
http://www.asiainitiatives.org/ 
https://www.womenstrong.org/people/susan-blaustein #metoo #metooindia

sebuah film biografi yang didasarkan pada kehidupan seorang bangsawan t-series gulshan kumar sedang dalam proses, tetapi sepertinya film ini menghadapi banyak rintangan. setelah sutradara film subhash kapoor dituduh dalam gerakan seksual #metoo yang sedang berlangsung, aamir khan yang ikut memproduksi film tersebut dikabarkan keluar dari proyek tersebut.

laporan terbaru di sekitar perkembangan film itu menunjukkan bahwa meskipun para pembuatnya belum menyelesaikan siapa yang akan mengarahkan film itu setelah subhash kapoor dikeluarkan, apa yang mereka tolak adalah pemeran utama wanita. rupanya, sonakshi sinha telah didekati untuk memainkan pemeran utama wanita film tersebut. 
sebuah sumber yang dekat dengan film itu mengungkapkan kepada media terkemuka, â€œsonakshi sinha telah didekati untuk itu. film ini kembali ke tahun 70-an dan 80-an, tim sedang mencari pahlawan wanita, yang bisa memancarkan getaran retro. ini peran kecil, tapi bermakna". sona hanya perlu syuting selama beberapa hari. ketika dia mendengar naskahnya, dia menyukainya dan memberi tahu bhushan bahwa dia akan melakukannya. meskipun aktris rowdy rathore itu belum secara resmi menandatangani film mogul, dikatakan bahwa dia sangat tertarik.

sona terakhir terlihat dalam film happy phir bhag jayegi pada agustus lalu. ğŸ˜‰

text:
if you have ever wondered why relationships between men and women are so strenuous in today's society look no further than to the programming that's been placed into the minds of the people since birth. in today's world we have reality tv showing women that they have to be fighting with people and boisterous in their opinions to earn "respect" but no one respects them. movies putting forth female empowerment at the detriment of the household (pop culture). we have the #metoo movement that is creating more toxic feminism than it is showcasing female strength. men are scared to be men and to assert their correct place in the relationship in the eyes of the creator. and saying these things is now considered "bad", the idea that genders have roles. this has created a society of men being subservient to women and women completely missing the boat in knowing men. scripturally, the most high god has clearly defined roles for men and women that if followed will result in loving and lasting relationships that prosper in many ways. now mind you, a majority of the responsibility is on the woman, for she is the maker of the home not just physically but also emotionally. her love is the comfort for a man. something he wants to run to. a rebellious spirit is what will make a man run from her. man's responsibility is to love his wife as he loves himself, but god and christ are above him on the scale. women must know this and respect this if she wishes to live in love and to prosper with her man. for your household is a kingdom, and if your kingdom is divided against itself it will fall. 
luke 11:17 kjv
but he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them, every kingdom divided against itself is brought to desolation; and a house divided against a house falleth.

1 peter 3:5-6 kjv
for after this manner in the old time the holy women also, who trusted in god, adorned themselves, being in subjection unto their own husbands: [6] even as sara obeyed abraham, calling him lord: whose daughters ye are, as long as ye do well, and are not afraid with any amazement.

#truth #follow4follow #likeforlike #god #relationships #man #woman #usa #america #love #sabbath #love

text:
#mylifematters 
it's hard for me to hear:
"you are so brave" "you have guts for telling your story" "you are so courageous"
it makes me uncomfortable to hear these. before you tell me otherwise, i am working on feeling humble, blessed, and accepting of these compliments. i was groomed at a young age to be compliant, to be passive, to follow rather then lead.

i have experienced every spectrum of the abuse wheel. made to feel little. unworthy. told that the world would be better if i weren't in it and i should just kill myself. my story runs like a talk show circus. murder for hire, stalking, i briefly had a sister wife, experienced bdsm, supernatural issues and more. 
i knew if i didn't leave that i wouldn't be alive to see the end of that year-2009. 
fast forward, i am living happily ever after, free, remarried to mr. awesome, we have a son together, i wrote my memoir about surviving abuse, and now i'm speaking out about my experiences to help others know there can be a life without violence. if you are trapped in an abusive cycle and need help send me a private message to chat.
stay safe! 
big hugs, mel

text:
"since shillong is a matrilineal society and having been brought up by my aunt and granny, i was always very sensitive to issues faced by women. but an incident that i can never forget is something that happened at the guwahati railway station. i was in 7th grade and my sister, aunt and i were taking the train. the train was yet to reach, so i went to get coffee for everyone. meanwhile, in my absence, while they were waiting, across the railway tracks in the opposite direction was a decently dressed man. he was at quite a distance, but they could make out that he was staring at them with his penis in his hand, constantly rubbing it. they were uncomfortable and complained to a cop on duty, but he didn't bother to act upon it. by the time i came back he was gone.

i was furious when i heard about it especially at the cop who just ignored the entire incident. at that time i knew it was wrong and now that i've grown up i would never want anyone to be in the receiving end of such awful acts", shares @dazil_vek from #guwahati.

would you also like to share your story? drop us a message. #hewonttease

the effects of physical & emotional abuse can live with you your whole life. it can cause you to do things you never thought you would. it can have you repeating the same mistakes over and over because you never fully process the hurt. it can make you believe thatâ€™s just who you are now. untrusting. unwanted.
.

.

text:
#facetofacefriday i've contemplated whether or not to share this so many times. i'm literally shaking as i type this out because i'm so nervous.ğŸ˜¥ sit back, this is going to be a long one....
.
october is national domestic violence awareness month. so as hard as it is for me to put my story out there, i feel obligated to use my platform to spread awareness.ğŸ“£
.
it started small. the occasional name here & there. the saying one thing then doing another, & being made to feel crazy when i spoke up about it. it was jealousy of me having a social life, while they said i was boring or overreacting when they did whatever, whenever, with whoever. it was being told my family & friends were horrible people who shouldn't be in our lives, while they always had their family close by, even living with us at times. it was telling me i wasn't allowed to have certain jobs or go certain places because i would "go pick up other men". it was my property being broken while they were upset. it was taking their paychecks to use for themselves, after i had already used mine to cover our bills. it was using silent treatment, deflection, and a whole lot of hurtful names to get what they wanted. it was always apologizing the day after with some flowers and/or a card. it was being told that they were so sorry and things would change... just for it to continue on.
.
there were plenty of red flags long before the first shove, but i was young.
plenty of signs before the first choke, but i was uneducated.
plenty of warnings before the first punch, but i was blinded by love.
.
i am blessed that a car full of strangers happened to be driving by at the right time and pulled him off of me. i am blessed that i walked away with only some bruises and a couple broken teeth. i am blessed that there was funding out there to cover the ambulance ride, hospital, and dental bills. i am blessed that there were volunteers to educate me on the cycle of abuse. i am blessed that i had family to support me, take care of my son, & pick me up from the hospital. i am so blessed i made it out of that relationship & am blessed happy today..... continued....â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸â¬‡ï¸

text:
tell your stories. tell your truth. keep talking. get mad. keep supporting other abuse survivors. a year after the birth of the #metoo movement, much has changed and nothing has changed. victim blaming is on the rise again having seen and experienced it myself from fans, friends, and other people @adamcroasdell has enlisted towards myself and his other victims shows me how malicious and unsafe this world can be for victims. using young impressionable fans to shame and silence his victims shows how far we have to go to make victims feel safe from these abusers. actions from them and him is #whyididntreport on top of living in fear of him and their threats. my silence gave him a thirst for more and younger victims. i realize and know wholeheartedly he will never stop. his fans, friends, and family are his accomplices by victim shaming and he shows no remorse for the pain he causes he feels proud. in other words, if youâ€™re waiting for them to make an apology, forget it. these men might regret getting caught. but expressing true remorse about the damage they caused isnâ€™t forthcoming. what most of them havenâ€™t lost is the conviction that since they are either celebrities, men in power from business to political power they have the right to treat women as they please, not the women we are to bow down live with the nightmare. i decided to no longer suffer in silence but men like adam croasdell we stand up to or say no to feel they are the real victims and, as such, do not need to change their behavior and continue the cycle of abuse making it worse and enlist others to abuse their victims. adam croasdell is one of the many men during the #metoo era included in some of the most shameful chapters in the history of the united states because it shows his complicity and what men of his caliber will do to hurt women and hide it. 
#nomore #adamcroasdell #eccarius #ignisscientia #lordbothwell #actor #voiceactor #ffxv #preacher #reign #vampire #supernatural #losangeles #women #supportwomen #timesup

text:
https://www.gofundme.com/senate-sins @satanicbayarea

i am a member of satanic bay area who is a rape survivor, i also witnessed my mother being raped and beaten at a young age. i was outraged by the kavanaugh confirmation on a level bordering on insanity. between the disgusting confirmation and the sickeningly true political cartoon that was published shortly after the confirmation of lady justice being raped by a republican, i was sent into an unstoppable rage. i needed to yell and scream as loud as possible that this action is horrific and wrong and shits all over survivors. 
the members of satanic bay area are moved to use our outrage to send a poignant letter with curses to the kavanaugh supporters in the senate. we also feel that in this time of outrage and disdain we need to support women's rights at the same time. this campaign was born to fuel the fire that is burning in all of our hearts and minds and add a voice to all of that rage. we are asking you to donate to help women who are in need of care and a safe place to go for help, therefore, all of the proceeds of this campaign will be donated to planned parenthood, short the fee that is taken by gofundme.

satanic bay area will be sending out a letter that we have written with an embedded curse to the senate members via fax. for each $1 donated we will send 1 faxed letter to the senate on halloween (10/31/18), therefore, this campaign will close at 10 a.m. pst on 10/31/18.

we know that you are just as outraged by this injustice as we are and implore you to help us spread the word that the confirmation of kavanaugh is disgustingly wrong and satanic bay area, myself, and most importantly, you, do not stand behind this action.

#metoo #plannedparenthood #atheist #atheism #satanic #curse #survivor #fuckkavanaugh #kavanagh #democrat #left #atheisticsatanism #satan #leftwing #prochoice

iâ€™m sorry on behalf of the system of toxic masculinity that iâ€™ve reaped the benefits and privilege of. 
iâ€™m sorry for the public nightmare that youâ€™ve had to endure these past few days, weeks, months, years and lifetimes.

i will fight every chance i get, in every space iâ€™m in, to make the world in a place that values the boundless power within you. 
i hope u know how loved u are.
**

text: last night i got into a heated conversation with a guy. let's just say it didn't go well. i have felt like i really need to share this portion of our conversation tho. if a man, or boy, ever tell you what to do, that is not ok. you are allowed to speak your mind and stand up for whoever and whatever you want! it's ok to stand up for yourself and it's people like this, who put women down, that make this world a bad place for women. so stop contribution to "keep women in the kitchen" and actually treat us with respect. #metoo #standupgirl #youaregoodenough

text:
it's funny how i was trying to fit in a picture for what i'm going to write down. but of course you don't get pictures that would fit in for such things.

i being a girl; born and brought up in india we're always taught how to live, how to react, how to be silent about things which aren't socially accepted because here the victim is wrong and not the accused. 
i come out in open and would say that yes i too have been sexually assaulted. #metoo 
whenever incidents like this happen with me or around me i just go numb. my mind and body stops reacting, i honestly take a lot of time to digest the fact that a human can to do this to another human. we have come out to be as predators. i barely understand how can human just grab a girl/guy without his or her concern? how can your fucking conscious allow that? 
these things take a lot of time for me to process inside me and i being a really strong personality yet i chose to be silent when such things happen because i don't really understand how does this happen and how to react and what to do!? some people would barely understand my reaction and some would relate to it but i'm this and i'll try to get better.
i've people who have tried forcing themselves up/touching me inappropriately etc. ofcourse without my consent following me on my instagram handle. and if you're reading this, i hope you're ashamed of what you did. try and be a better human or rather try fitting in the word "human" and control your fucking horses. 
i hope every one tries to gather up some courage and speak up. i hope next time something like this happens to me or around me i've the courage to fight back.
#metoo

text: my one goal for 2018 was to finish the book i started writing 4 years ago. i did (woot) and queried 50 literary agents over the past 6 months. that has not been going great and i have a feeling itâ€™s because what i wrote is too long by about 40,000+ words. so, iâ€™m putting a pause button on queries and am re-visiting my story to make edits. i joined a writers group on fb and iâ€™m being my own cheerleader about all of this because i think this is good (and i rarely think that about my own fiction) and itâ€™s relevant af because itâ€™s about #metoo. that hashtag is nowhere in the book because i wrote most of it 4 years ago. most of the really bad metoo-related experiences of my life happened between my teens and before grad school, but the frequency of harassment and whatnot escalated when i moved to nyc. i began questioning why i was the target of all of this crap. why did this stuff keep happening to me when i go out of my way to avoid attention? and so i wrote a fictionalized version of that into this book as an outlet for my questions and frustrations because 4 years ago, sexual harassment and assault wasnâ€™t everyday conversation like it is now. i didnâ€™t know that a majority of other women went through this too. i sure as shit do now, though. and iâ€™m grateful for it, as heartbreaking as itâ€™s been to hear everyoneâ€™s stories. earlier this week, there was an associated press article about the year since #metoo. they interviewed four people from across the country and i was asked to be involved. i even ended up being the lead image and story for the piece (swipe right if you donâ€™t believe me...). so, my real story is out in the world... now i need to get my fictional one out there too. iâ€™m a great editor when it comes to other peopleâ€™s work, but this is a challenge. iâ€™m glad to take it on, though. plus, iâ€™m stubborn af. i love this book with my whole heart and am going to get it published somehow. if anyone wants to read it and provide notes, lemme know. itâ€™s contemporary ya fiction and the main characters are college freshmen. #writing #workinprogress #seekingrepresentation #editing #yafiction #fiction #fictionwriting #seekingliteraryagent
